    "4fd3a6a8-8ece-4aea-9857-8c69338c72cc": {
      "type": "rich-text-4",
      "custom_css": [
        ".about-collection-banner-title h2 {text-transform: none;}",
        ".subtitle {padding: 40px 0 0 0px; background-color: transparent;}",
        ".rich-text-4 {margin-bottom: 0px;}"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "custom_class": "about-collection-banner-title subtitle",
        "prefix": "",
        "section_title": "TIME TO PUT YOUR SHOES ON AND WALK IT OFF!",
        "section_sub": "",
        "description": "<p>Now, you had your breakfast and it's time to really have a chilled morning scrolling around Lisbon, taking that perfect shot with its beauty (Instagram as you please)!                             <br/><br/><br/><br/></p>",
        "section_url": ""
      }
    },
    "custom_image_with_text_YUmJTN": {
      "type": "custom-image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_iJ7QHp": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>One of the places we suggest? </p><h6></h6><p>Obviously, LX Factory in Alcântara – the spot where creativity ignites, and an old industrial complex is reborn as a vibrant hub.</p><h6></h6><p> No wonder we have our offices here, right? Full disclosure: it's a tourist hub, but it's one that is always worth visiting and exploring.</p><h6></h6><p> Think graffiti-covered walls, quirky boutiques, and street performances – a haven where creativity thrives. </p><h6></h6><p>Discover hidden gems like indie bookshops (hello to our friends at Ler Devagar), design studios, \\pop-up galleries, and world food (if you're full from breakfast we get it).</p>",
            "text_style": "subtitle"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_iJ7QHp"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "custom_class": "about-us-content responsibility-section-four",
        "desktop-image": "shopify://shop_images/4-LX-Factory-_960x960px.jpg",
        "mob-image": "shopify://shop_images/4-LX-Factory-_960x960px_c2eaf2f9-1e8d-4b18-ae05-b4043fcddefb.jpg",
        "height": "adapt",
        "desktop_image_width": "medium",
        "layout": "image_first",
        "desktop_content_position": "top",
        "desktop_content_alignment": "left",
        "content_layout": "no-overlap",
        "color_scheme": "background-1",
        "mobile_content_alignment": "left",
        "padding_top": 12,
        "padding_bottom": 0
      }
    },
    "custom_image_with_text_zdqPkW": {
      "type": "custom-image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_KNaEP9": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Museums in Lisbon are a must (go visit your local museums!), and of course, we'll suggest Museu Nacional de Arte Antiga (near Santos), a place for a 5000-year art time travel journey. </p><h6></h6><p>You can find everything from Ancient Egypt to modern 20th-century masterpieces. Rembrandt, Turner, and Monet breathe and conquer the eyes of guests within the museum's walls.</p><h6></h6><p>Explore Egyptian wonders guided by Howard Carter's insights, admire Greek coins curated by E.S.G. Robinson, and revel in the Far East allure with porcelains, lacquers, and prints from China and Japan. </p><h6></h6><p>A cultural wonder perfect for a cultural morning.</p><p></p><p></p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_KNaEP9"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "custom_class": "about-us-content responsibility-section-four",
        "desktop-image": "shopify://shop_images/5-Relleno-generativo-_960x960px_a7a241ec-d2c1-492c-87b1-f237a68ab662.jpg",
        "mob-image": "shopify://shop_images/5-Relleno-generativo-_960x960px.jpg",
        "height": "adapt",
        "desktop_image_width": "medium",
        "layout": "text_first",
        "desktop_content_position": "top",
        "desktop_content_alignment": "left",
        "content_layout": "no-overlap",
        "color_scheme": "background-1",
        "mobile_content_alignment": "left",
        "padding_top": 0,
        "padding_bottom": 16
      }
    },
    "custom_image_with_text_UVb3hC": {
      "type": "custom-image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_RhKCE4": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Or you can plan your cultural morning stroll and enter the world of Calouste Sarkis Gulbenkian's private collection, where European artistry meets Eastern opulence near Praça de Espanha. </p><h6></h6><p>Discover the works of master artists like Renoir, Manet, and Romney, alongside exquisite Persian textiles, Turkish ceramics, and Islamic art. Take a journey through time with pieces inspired by Tutankhamun that reflect the influence of Howard Carter. </p><h6></h6><p>You'll also find elegant 16th-century tapestries and French jewelry that exude a pure opulence. </p><h6></h6><p>Come and experience the legacy of a great collector, where beauty and wonder await.</p>",
            "text_style": "subtitle"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_RhKCE4"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "custom_class": "about-us-content responsibility-section-four",
        "desktop-image": "shopify://shop_images/6-Gulbenkian-_960x960px_27f0c2bc-364e-47a4-a137-a9ed84e72e39.jpg",
        "mob-image": "shopify://shop_images/6-Gulbenkian-_960x960px.jpg",
        "height": "adapt",
        "desktop_image_width": "medium",
        "layout": "image_first",
        "desktop_content_position": "top",
        "desktop_content_alignment": "left",
        "content_layout": "no-overlap",
        "color_scheme": "background-1",
        "mobile_content_alignment": "left",
        "padding_top": 12,
        "padding_bottom": 0
      }
    },
    "rich_text_4_JEKyJN": {
      "type": "rich-text-4",
      "settings": {
        "custom_class": "about-collection-banner-title page-banner-title",
        "prefix": "",
        "section_title": "A BREAK FOR LUNCH?",
